-No.

05:49.914 --> 05:51.481
I'm going to do it.

05:51.525 --> 05:53.178
You're forcing my fingers
of truth.

05:53.222 --> 05:55.485
-No. No.
-It's happening.

05:55.529 --> 05:57.095
-No. No.
-I'm going to.

05:57.139 --> 05:58.488
-Here I go! I'm going to!
-No, no, Paul!

05:58.532 --> 05:59.794
-Paul, no... No, no...
-I'm going to...

05:59.837 --> 06:01.273
I'll punch you in the balls.

06:01.317 --> 06:02.579
-I'll punch you in the balls.
-Don't do that.

06:02.623 --> 06:04.494
-[laughing]
-Don't do it.

06:09.194 --> 06:11.283
[car honking]

06:11.327 --> 06:14.678
Do you think we did
the right thing moving here?

06:14.722 --> 06:17.115
Yeah, [stammers]
of course we did.

06:17.159 --> 06:18.508
I mean, look at us. We're...

06:18.552 --> 06:21.293
This is like you're,
you're in your dream job

06:21.337 --> 06:24.035
and we're in this
radical apartment,

06:24.079 --> 06:25.820
we just started eating pizza.

06:25.863 --> 06:26.951
Yeah.

06:29.389 --> 06:33.044
Why do you think
the rent is so cheap?

06:33.088 --> 06:34.481
It's like you always say,
you know,

06:34.524 --> 06:37.222
"Sometimes you just get lucky."

06:37.266 --> 06:38.267
Hm...

06:39.921 --> 06:41.052
Yeah.

06:47.319 --> 06:50.235
[wind howling]

06:52.760 --> 06:55.676
[eerie music]

07:02.900 --> 07:06.077
-Oh, God.
-Do you yield?

07:06.121 --> 07:07.601
What?

07:08.689 --> 07:10.125
[shouting] Do you yield?

07:10.168 --> 07:13.650
-No.
-What is your book?

07:13.694 --> 07:16.914
I... [stammers]
What?

07:16.958 --> 07:19.177
Ah! The Book Of Iowa.

07:19.221 --> 07:22.485
I select verse 23!

07:22.529 --> 07:24.574
"And the police
had no solid lead.

07:24.618 --> 07:28.360
The investigation being further
hampered by the suspect's sketch

07:28.404 --> 07:29.666
of a tall Indian man!"

07:29.710 --> 07:32.756
-What?
-Yes! I win!

07:32.800 --> 07:35.367
[grunting]

07:35.411 --> 07:38.327
[intense music]

07:40.416 --> 07:43.332
[mumbling]

07:50.557 --> 07:51.906
[grunting]

07:51.949 --> 07:54.212
Ah. Oh, what...

07:54.256 --> 07:56.519
No! [whimpering]

07:56.563 --> 07:58.303
-Do you yield?
-Yes!

07:58.347 --> 07:59.870
[grunting]

07:59.914 --> 08:02.220
-That's a cake knife.
-So what?

08:02.264 --> 08:04.005
Oh, God! Oh, God!

08:04.048 --> 08:06.007
Claire!

08:06.050 --> 08:08.052
Claire! Claire! Let me in!

08:08.096 --> 08:09.401
Oh, God! Oh, God!

08:09.445 --> 08:12.056
Oh, God! Oh, my God!

08:12.100 --> 08:14.232
[Claire screaming]

08:14.276 --> 08:17.105
No! Oh, God, God!

08:17.148 --> 08:18.236
Oh, God!

08:18.280 --> 08:20.674
[Claire screaming]

08:20.717 --> 08:24.591
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

08:24.634 --> 08:27.115
Are you all right?
Are you all right?

08:27.158 --> 08:29.857
-Oh, no! Oh, no!
-[siren wailing in distance]

08:29.900 --> 08:32.163
What do we do?

08:32.207 --> 08:33.904
-[camera clicks]
-[indistinct radio chatter]

08:33.948 --> 08:35.818
[Cartwright sighs]

08:35.863 --> 08:38.779
Okay, Wallace, enough!

08:38.822 --> 08:41.563
I-i-it's photographed.
He's standing still.

08:41.607 --> 08:44.828
Goddammit!
That flash gives me migraines.

08:44.872 --> 08:47.875
You need 900 pictures?
Are you makin' a 3D model?

08:47.918 --> 08:50.791
-[camera clicks]
-[sighs]

08:50.834 --> 08:52.836
All right, I'm gonna need
to take your statements.

08:52.880 --> 08:54.011
Just tell me everything
that you know

08:54.055 --> 08:56.884
in your own words, Mr., uh...

08:56.927 --> 08:59.060
Boyd. Paul Boyd.

08:59.103 --> 09:00.278
And you're Mrs. Boyd?

09:00.322 --> 09:01.976
Oh, no,
we're, we're not married.

09:02.019 --> 09:05.501
[mumbles] Claire and I need
to get our things sorted.

09:05.545 --> 09:06.850
Mm.

09:08.460 --> 09:11.376
[thudding]

09:17.034 --> 09:20.516
All right. You kids have fun.

09:20.560 --> 09:24.520
Wait a second. A guy just
killed himself in our bathtub.

09:24.564 --> 09:27.349
-Yeah.
-Why?

09:27.392 --> 09:28.872
[sighs]

09:30.526 --> 09:33.355
From time to time,
members of a deranged cult

09:33.398 --> 09:34.791
break and enter
into this dwelling

09:34.835 --> 09:36.445
in order to commit self-murder.

09:36.488 --> 09:37.925
Did the super
not go over this with you

09:37.968 --> 09:39.056
when you looked
at the apartment?

09:39.100 --> 09:40.101
[knocking on door]

09:40.144 --> 09:42.407
Knock, knock! Hi!

09:42.451 --> 09:44.584
Hello, Beatrice.
You're looking wonderful.

09:44.627 --> 09:46.586
And you are looking great,
Bloyce.

09:46.629 --> 09:47.891
-Stop it.
-[chuckling]

09:47.935 --> 09:51.068
-Oh, here you go.
-Oh, what's this?

09:51.112 --> 09:53.941
Oh, I always buy my tenants
a carrot cake

09:53.984 --> 09:57.509
for their first tub death.
It's just a little tradition.

09:57.553 --> 10:00.774
-"Their first tub death?"
-Save me a piece. [chuckles]

10:00.817 --> 10:03.820
I'm making fish sticks later.

10:03.864 --> 10:05.648
Look, honestly, these cultist

10:05.692 --> 10:07.171
t-they're basically harmless.

10:07.215 --> 10:09.783
Their only goal
is an exit strategy.

10:12.220 --> 10:14.352
Are they that different?
What am I doing?

10:14.396 --> 10:15.919
I really do have to go.

10:15.963 --> 10:18.139
Hey! You can't just leave.

10:18.182 --> 10:20.532
We're totally exposed here.

10:20.576 --> 10:22.317
You're totally exposed?

10:22.360 --> 10:25.886
I'm the one that has to clean up
this mess night after night.

10:25.929 --> 10:28.497
Do you think this is how
I planned to spend my evening?

10:28.540 --> 10:31.674
I'm planned to be home
working on my screenplay.

10:31.718 --> 10:33.981
I just got a note that the
detective character doesn't have

10:34.024 --> 10:36.331
enough conflict.
I'm a detective.

10:36.374 --> 10:38.768
It's a screenplay
about a detective.

10:38.812 --> 10:40.378
There's conflict.

10:40.422 --> 10:43.207
This industry is bullshit.

10:43.251 --> 10:47.647
The point is,
instead, I'm here.

10:47.690 --> 10:50.345
More often then you guys,
by the way.

10:52.086 --> 10:53.304
Good luck.

10:54.784 --> 10:56.786
What do we do now?

10:56.830 --> 10:59.223
If I were you, I'd move!

10:59.267 --> 11:02.183
[instrumental music]

11:04.228 --> 11:07.144
[Claire sobbing]

11:08.493 --> 11:13.020
Hey. Hey, hey, hey, hey.

11:13.063 --> 11:16.023
Look on the bright side.

11:16.066 --> 11:18.678
Maybe now we can try Winnipeg.

11:20.114 --> 11:23.030
[sobbing]

11:27.687 --> 11:30.602
[keyboard keys clacking]

11:36.173 --> 11:39.089
[eerie music]

12:12.296 --> 12:15.517
