12:29.618 --> 12:33.665
♪ The instantaneous eternity

12:35.145 --> 12:38.801
♪ The instantaneous eternity

12:38.845 --> 12:41.761
[water gurgling]

12:45.112 --> 12:48.028
[instrumental music]

12:55.644 --> 12:56.645
Mm...

12:58.386 --> 13:00.867
[water gurgling]

13:00.910 --> 13:03.826
[operatic singing]

13:19.233 --> 13:21.017
[man] Claire.

13:24.586 --> 13:26.980
Come to me, my child.

13:29.939 --> 13:32.855
[music continues]

13:35.597 --> 13:37.555
Claire.

13:44.562 --> 13:46.913
Yeah, that's it.

13:54.355 --> 13:56.531
Ah, yeah.

14:03.103 --> 14:04.887
[children laughing]

14:06.236 --> 14:09.152
[dramatic music]

14:25.865 --> 14:29.390
Wake up! Wake up, Paul!
Wake up! [chuckling]

14:29.433 --> 14:31.435
-Come on.
-I'm up, I'm up, I'm up...

14:31.479 --> 14:33.916
I was up all night
and I had a revelation.

14:33.960 --> 14:35.396
-You did? What is it?
-Yeah.

14:35.439 --> 14:37.746
We aren't going anywhere.

14:37.789 --> 14:39.095
-We're not?
-No.

14:39.139 --> 14:41.097
-We're not?
-No, because we're in LA.

14:41.141 --> 14:42.969
It's like
the land of, of movie stars

14:43.012 --> 14:44.884
and fancy cars, you know?

14:44.927 --> 14:46.798
There's like five places alone
on this block

14:46.842 --> 14:48.931
where you can get kombucha.

14:48.975 --> 14:50.715
What's that? What is kombucha?

14:50.759 --> 14:53.022
I don't even know.
A-and that's my point.

14:53.066 --> 14:55.024
You know, 'cause if
we're gonna be LA-ians,

14:55.068 --> 14:57.679
we-we gotta,
we gotta adapt, right?

14:57.722 --> 14:59.811
Yeah, yes, yes, I do know,

14:59.855 --> 15:02.771
what you, like a, mm,
like an adaptation.

15:02.814 --> 15:04.991
Yes, and we-we're,
we're not just gonna run away

15:05.034 --> 15:07.863
because some idiots wanna spill
their guts in our bathtub.

15:07.907 --> 15:10.910
No, no. This is our dream,
this is our destiny.

15:10.953 --> 15:13.390
Yes, I don't wanna run, Claire.

15:13.434 --> 15:15.958
I'm, I'm... Like you always say,
I'm lazy.

15:16.002 --> 15:19.179
We are strong
and we are, we are adaptable

15:19.222 --> 15:22.051
and we are,
we are Los Angelenos.

15:22.095 --> 15:25.663
Oh, gosh, dang it. I love you.

15:25.707 --> 15:28.188
-I love you.
-I love you, too.

15:28.231 --> 15:29.667
-I love you, Claire.
-[chuckles]

15:29.711 --> 15:31.626
-Let me go back to bed, though.
-Oh, no.

15:31.669 --> 15:34.194
[car engine rumbling]

15:34.237 --> 15:37.675
Claire, this meeting started
15 minutes ago.

15:37.719 --> 15:41.636
I am so sorry, some guy broke
into our apartment last night

15:41.679 --> 15:43.333
and then committed suicide
in the bathtub.

15:43.377 --> 15:44.987
I-I think he was like,
part of some cult.

15:45.031 --> 15:46.336
The cult of Storsh.

15:46.380 --> 15:49.035
You're living in
the Tabula Building? Why?

15:49.078 --> 15:51.254
Great location,
it's close to freeways.

15:51.298 --> 15:53.996
Moving on. Meegan Nordheim.

15:54.040 --> 15:58.000
You all know her, star
of the reality show Meal Ticket,

15:58.044 --> 15:59.915
stands to inherit
half a billion dollars

15:59.959 --> 16:02.918
from insecticide king,
Armund Nordheim,

16:02.962 --> 16:06.095
who is currently 96 years old

16:06.139 --> 16:08.141
and counting.

16:08.184 --> 16:10.795
And she is now
running for congress

16:10.839 --> 16:12.841
because that's a thing now.

16:12.884 --> 16:14.364
The woman's a monster.

16:14.408 --> 16:16.366
Yeah. She wants an increase
in kill shelters.

16:16.410 --> 16:18.455
I mean, who campaigns
on killing puppies?

16:18.499 --> 16:21.023
She's retained us at the rate of
50,000 a month.

16:21.067 --> 16:23.025
-She has my full support.
-Our country needs her.

16:23.069 --> 16:25.027
Yeah, well, she was up
in the polls as of last night,

16:25.071 --> 16:27.247
but all that's gonna change
because this morning

16:27.290 --> 16:31.164
the Los Angeles Tatlerran
this series of paparazzi photos

16:31.207 --> 16:34.471
showing Ms. Nordheim
enjoying the company

16:34.515 --> 16:39.433
of 20-year-old personal trainer
slash actor, Dake Wharton.

16:39.476 --> 16:42.740
-Oh, my God.
-Is that a squash?

16:42.784 --> 16:45.091
Look, this one's easy. It's a
classic redirect.

16:45.134 --> 16:47.354
She repents, goes to church
every Sunday,

16:47.397 --> 16:51.053
does a couple of guest sermons,
talks about rebirth through God.

16:51.097 --> 16:52.446
Somethin' there. Tony.

16:52.489 --> 16:53.795
[Tony] I mean, I say,
we blame the dude.

16:53.838 --> 16:55.666
Nordheim
was manipulated

16:55.710 --> 16:59.757
by some Hollywood pretty boy
who preys on middle-aged women

16:59.801 --> 17:01.629
in order to extort money
for sex.

17:01.672 --> 17:03.413
Okay, she is the victim here.

17:05.894 --> 17:10.290
-Claire?
-Uh... Um...

17:10.333 --> 17:12.944
[sighs]

17:12.988 --> 17:14.685
When I was in eight grade

17:14.729 --> 17:18.472
Ben Barnes, he drew private
parts on my notebook,

17:18.515 --> 17:20.430
but I-I put stickers
over top of them

17:20.473 --> 17:21.866
and I turned them into unicorn.

