and-and then that... that got
into the town's water supply.

32:23.071 --> 32:26.901
[sobbing] And the entire town
lost their hair.

32:29.208 --> 32:30.731
All their hair.

32:30.774 --> 32:33.864
Their arms and their legs
and their eyebrows.

32:33.908 --> 32:38.608
And then... and then
about half the town,

32:38.652 --> 32:40.915
let's say, about 80,000 people,

32:40.959 --> 32:43.874
got rage madness and they
started foaming at the mouth

32:43.918 --> 32:46.051
and attacking each other
for no reason.

32:46.094 --> 32:49.271
And then the whole town
became a war zone.

32:49.315 --> 32:52.318
And we had to stay inside,
but everybody got so hungry.

32:52.361 --> 32:54.450
But then the rage people
stole all the food

32:54.494 --> 32:57.018
and they, they hid it
in a used tire yard.

32:57.062 --> 33:01.457
And they built this massive fort
out of used tires.

33:01.501 --> 33:04.330
It was like a beehive,
and then they stayed in,

33:04.373 --> 33:06.201
in the tire hive
and they wouldn't come out.

33:06.245 --> 33:07.811
And so then all the [stammering]

33:07.855 --> 33:09.639
then the normal people
burned down the tire hive.

33:09.683 --> 33:12.555
But then the fire,
the fire burned for months

33:12.599 --> 33:15.689
because it was just
millions of used tires.

33:15.732 --> 33:17.734
[sobbing] And then
we all had to go to the woods

33:17.778 --> 33:19.345
and hunt for animals.

33:19.388 --> 33:21.347
But it was the summer
and, and it was so hot

33:21.390 --> 33:24.132
and we all took off
all of our, our clothes

33:24.176 --> 33:26.265
and then we ran out of bullets.

33:26.308 --> 33:29.616
And so there's just a bunch
of hairless naked people

33:29.659 --> 33:32.880
running around the woods,
hunting for deer

33:32.923 --> 33:36.231
and raccoons and squirrels
with our bare hands.

33:36.275 --> 33:39.234
And then, t-then everyone

33:39.278 --> 33:42.672
got really hungry again
'cause we ran out of animals.

33:42.716 --> 33:47.068
And then... then you couldn't
tell the normal people

33:47.112 --> 33:48.852
from the rage people

33:48.896 --> 33:51.681
and-and you couldn't tell
who was who.

33:51.725 --> 33:53.292
And then a militia came
from another state

33:53.335 --> 33:55.337
and they called us all
s-skinners

33:55.381 --> 33:58.166
and th-they hunted us for sport.

33:58.210 --> 34:01.387
And then the National Guard
came to fight the militia

34:01.430 --> 34:04.085
and then the government
sent in the army

34:04.129 --> 34:06.479
[sobbing] to rescue us all

34:06.522 --> 34:09.525
and then when it was all done...

34:09.569 --> 34:12.353
they told me I couldn't go back
to Ohio anymore.

34:14.052 --> 34:15.966
[sobbing]

34:18.404 --> 34:20.232
Oh, Paul.

34:20.275 --> 34:22.755
Sounds like you've been
on quite the journey.

34:22.799 --> 34:24.409
But your true journey of bliss

34:24.453 --> 34:26.498
found
on the instantaneous eternity

34:26.542 --> 34:29.415
only begins
when you change your story.

34:29.458 --> 34:32.373
It's time to loose the Os
in Ohio

34:32.418 --> 34:34.942
and say hito the new Paul,

34:34.985 --> 34:38.989
a Paul who's his own boss,
a Paul who answers to Paul.

34:39.033 --> 34:40.513
To-to me?

34:40.556 --> 34:42.123
[Bird] It's like
the Book Of Storiessays.

34:42.167 --> 34:45.518
The only thing you've to worry
about is what you think.

34:45.561 --> 34:48.303
If there's no job for you,
make your own job.

34:48.347 --> 34:52.264
Be like me. Be free.
Free like a bird, bird.

34:53.178 --> 34:56.398
Free? Like a bird, bird?

34:56.442 --> 34:57.704
[birds chirping]

34:57.747 --> 34:59.749
[whispers] Like a bird, bird.

35:00.663 --> 35:01.838
Yeah.

35:08.976 --> 35:10.282
-[doorknob rattles]
-[Claire] Hey-hey!

35:10.325 --> 35:13.067
-Hey!
-I had the best day.

35:13.111 --> 35:14.851
Me, too.
I had, I have huge news.

35:14.895 --> 35:16.114
Oh, okay. You first.

35:16.157 --> 35:17.767
So I-I slammed the door

35:17.811 --> 35:19.160
on the jackals of over-thoughts.

35:19.204 --> 35:20.683
Just like you said,
I've been so worried

35:20.727 --> 35:22.076
about what everyone else thinks
I should be

35:22.120 --> 35:24.078
that I forgot what I want to be.

35:24.122 --> 35:25.906
Oh, well, that-that's amazing.
What do you wanna be, Paul?

35:25.949 --> 35:28.169
A bird housemaker.

35:28.213 --> 35:30.606
I make birdhouses now.

35:30.650 --> 35:32.695
Come, come, come.

35:32.739 --> 35:35.307
Oh, wow!
You, you made all of these?

35:35.350 --> 35:36.917
Yeah, I'm in the zone.

35:36.960 --> 35:38.919
Look, so this one's
a little pool house, right?

35:38.962 --> 35:40.747
And it's got a little lounge
chair, a little changing room

35:40.790 --> 35:42.531
where the birds can change
out of their red clothes.

35:42.575 --> 35:44.185
A simple
mother-daughter apartment

35:44.229 --> 35:46.013
for when mom gets really old
and she could die,

35:46.056 --> 35:47.493
she could die at any moment.

35:47.536 --> 35:48.711
There's a little
mechanical chair

35:48.755 --> 35:50.191
that goes up and down the
stairs.

35:50.235 --> 35:51.714
This one is modelled
after Chuck E. Cheese,

35:51.758 --> 35:53.368
but I call it Chick E. Cheese.

35:53.412 --> 35:55.196
And there's a little bosspit.

35:55.240 --> 35:57.155
And there's a fake band and then
this one is a honeymoon suite,

35:57.198 --> 36:01.202
it's got a, um, a heart-shaped
bed for getting it on.

36:01.246 --> 36:05.598
Oh, look.
Claire, I almost forgot.

36:05.641 --> 36:08.253
This one's for you.

36:08.296 --> 36:10.994
It's an exact replica scale

36:11.038 --> 36:13.171
of the Full Houseliving room,
season one.

36:13.214 --> 36:16.565
Paul, this is, this is amazing!

36:16.609 --> 36:18.045
You don't have to say that.

36:18.088 --> 36:21.570
No, Paul. No.
I-I'm really proud of you.

36:23.050 --> 36:24.747
-Mm.
-Thank you.

36:26.836 --> 36:28.229
-Tell me about your day!
-Oh--

36:28.273 --> 36:30.144
I can't believe.
I've been so focused on, I...

36:30.188 --> 36:31.624
What about your day?
Take the mic.

36:31.667 --> 36:33.756
-Okay.
-[laughs]

36:33.800 --> 36:35.758
-[clicking] Is it on? Okay.
-[laughs] You...

36:35.802 --> 36:37.456
Um, so, yeah, we had this,
the surprise visit

36:37.499 --> 36:39.849
from a client at work and
everyone was, like, stressed out

36:39.893 --> 36:42.504
and losing their minds, but I
kept my cool and I saved the day

36:42.548 --> 36:44.506
with a stunning pitch
when everyone else had nothing.

36:44.550 --> 36:46.247
-And Pearl even shook my hand.
-That hand?

36:46.291 --> 36:47.248
-Yeah!
-All right! [laughs]

36:47.292 --> 36:48.771
I knew you could do it!

36:48.815 --> 36:50.556
You know, and I-I just applied
the teachings

36:50.599 --> 36:52.166
of Storsh
and it actually worked.

36:52.210 --> 36:54.473
-Oh, my God. I love Storsh.
-Yeah, I know. Me, too.

36:54.516 --> 36:56.779
I'm so jacked up right now,
I can sell anything.

36:56.823 --> 36:59.217
-Well, sell me a birdhouse.
-How about a pun?

36:59.260 --> 37:01.958
Like, uh, Paul's birdhouse,
when nature Pauls.

37:02.002 --> 37:03.308
-That's brilliant!
-[laughs]

37:03.351 --> 37:04.918
Okay, here's another...
Uh, uh...

37:04.961 --> 37:07.703
This birdhouse
will never Paul out of a tree.

37:07.747 --> 37:09.444
You gotta slow down. I gotta
write this down. Seriously. I--

37:09.488 --> 37:11.403
Oh, no, no. Don't even sweat it.
I got a million of 'em.

37:11.446 --> 37:13.492
Okay, how about this one?
Uh, uh, Paul's Boyd...

37:13.535 --> 37:15.581
Paul Boyd's birdie
birdhouse building.

37:15.624 --> 37:17.757
-Ah! You know what your name is?
-What?

37:17.800 --> 37:19.193
-Little Ms. Ideas. Yes.
-No.

37:19.237 --> 37:20.281
-You're amazing.
-No, you're amazing.

37:20.325 --> 37:21.500
-We're amazing.
-Yeah.

37:21.543 --> 37:22.936
You know what this means,
Claire?

37:22.979 --> 37:24.764
We're finally
getting our stuff sorted.

37:24.807 --> 37:25.982
Yeah.

37:26.940 --> 37:29.029
[moaning]

37:37.255 --> 37:38.604
[rattling]

37:42.216 --> 37:44.305
It was the '90s,

37:44.349 --> 37:47.526
a different time,
a simpler time.

37:47.569 --> 37:50.964
When a man committed a crime,
you kicked in the door

37:51.007 --> 37:53.532
and worried about paperwork
later.

37:55.490 --> 37:57.405
But like all good times,

37:57.449 --> 37:59.625
that time was a time

37:59.668 --> 38:02.497
whose time has come to an end.

38:04.847 --> 38:08.068
[Cartwright] Then on April 2nd,
1997,

38:08.111 --> 38:11.767
I came face-to-face
with pure evil.

38:11.811 --> 38:13.378
Reginald Euclid Storsh,

38:13.421 --> 38:15.728
incited over
two dozen innocent victims

38:15.771 --> 38:17.425
to self-murder.

38:17.469 --> 38:20.341
An adversary so brilliant,
so cunning

38:20.385 --> 38:22.038
that to merely be
in his presence

38:22.082 --> 38:23.692
was to risk total mental

38:23.736 --> 38:26.347
and spiritual annihilation.

38:26.391 --> 38:29.263
"Detective Cartwright,
did you have a warrant

38:29.307 --> 38:31.004
for these proceedings?"

38:31.047 --> 38:34.442
"A warrant? Hell, no,
Your Honor, he's guilty."

38:34.486 --> 38:37.402
"Well, I don't care
how ridiculous or stupid

38:37.445 --> 38:40.318
or unfair it is,
I declare a mistrial.

38:40.361 --> 38:42.145
Case dismissed."

38:42.189 --> 38:44.539
"Your Honor, no!"

38:44.583 --> 38:46.889
So I made my life's goal up

38:46.933 --> 38:49.544
to not give him
a moment's rest.

38:49.588 --> 38:51.720
I dogged him like a dog.

38:51.764 --> 38:54.854
But six months into it,
he committed suicide

38:54.897 --> 38:56.508
in a bath tub.

38:56.551 --> 38:58.945
Then his followers started
committing suicide

38:58.988 --> 39:00.076
in the same tub.

39:00.120 --> 39:02.122
Cultist after cultist

39:02.165 --> 39:04.385
dove into a porcelain nightmare

39:04.429 --> 39:06.779
of blood and death.

39:06.822 --> 39:09.347
The chief
still has the case open.

39:09.390 --> 39:11.000
And guess who has to clean up

39:11.044 --> 39:13.133
every time one of these morons

39:13.176 --> 39:15.744
commits a see-pa-coo
in the tub?

39:15.788 --> 39:18.704
That's right. Me. Cartwright.

39:18.747 --> 39:20.749
The last good cop.

39:33.632 --> 39:35.068
[window opens]

39:36.461 --> 39:38.854
Go, go, go, go, go, go.
Go, go, go.

39:38.898 --> 39:41.770
[instrumental music]

39:47.472 --> 39:48.603
[sighs]

39:57.612 --> 39:59.832
-Hey.
-Mm!

39:59.875 --> 40:02.835
Oh... Oh, come on, man!

40:02.878 --> 40:05.315
-What?
-I booked the tub!

40:05.359 --> 40:07.579
It's been on the schedule
for months.

40:07.622 --> 40:10.277
Okay. Just do it.

40:10.320 --> 40:13.672
Three-way challenge.
Do you yield?

40:13.715 --> 40:15.674
I-I, I don't, I don't know.
Do we?

40:19.329 --> 40:20.635
The invocation.

40:20.679 --> 40:22.463
"In order to get
to instantaneous eternity,

40:22.507 --> 40:23.899
you must pass through
the gateway

40:23.943 --> 40:25.771
chosen by the Holy Storsh."

40:29.949 --> 40:34.040
What? Oh, my God!
You're initiates, aren't you?

40:34.083 --> 40:35.955
Uh, initiates. Yeah.

40:35.998 --> 40:38.392
Actually, do you, do you
think you could teach us

40:38.436 --> 40:40.612
some initiate stuff?

40:43.832 --> 40:47.009
Well, maybe I'll break the rules
this one time.

40:47.053 --> 40:48.663
[laughing]

40:48.707 --> 40:50.404
-[Claire] Awesome.
-Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

40:50.448 --> 40:54.321
All right, um, you know,
you two guys really lucked out.

40:54.364 --> 40:57.672
It's not every day
that two initiates

40:57.716 --> 41:00.240
get taught their invocation

41:00.283 --> 41:02.416
by a level-six instructor.

41:02.460 --> 41:03.678
-Level six?
-Yeah.

41:03.722 --> 41:05.071
Is that, uh,
is that a good level?

41:05.114 --> 41:06.812
Uh, there's only 11 levels

41:06.855 --> 41:09.858
and I'm level six,
which is basically level seven,

41:09.902 --> 41:11.425
so really I'm an eight.

41:11.469 --> 41:14.559
So, yeah,
I'd say it's pretty damn good.

41:14.602 --> 41:17.605
And I specialize
in invocation training.

41:17.649 --> 41:20.086
You could say
I'm kind of a big deal

41:20.129 --> 41:21.827
down at East Side Bethel,
you know?

41:21.870 --> 41:23.306
-Huh. Mm!
-[Cultist] Okay.

41:23.350 --> 41:25.265
-Uh, so lie down.
-All right.

41:25.308 --> 41:26.919
Here.

41:26.962 --> 41:29.704
Okay. Like the...

41:29.748 --> 41:34.448
Uh, okay, um, scooch down
towards me a little.

41:34.492 --> 41:36.755
Okay, now go left, uh,
just a little bit.

41:36.798 --> 41:38.757
Okay. Actually, scooch back up
just a couple of...

41:38.800 --> 41:41.020
Yeah, okay, that's good.
And come over to your right.

41:41.063 --> 41:42.412
Okay, you're moving faster,
so, so just...

41:42.456 --> 41:43.413
-Yeah. And then...
-Me? Oh. Okay.

41:43.457 --> 41:45.111
You come down just a touch.

41:45.154 --> 41:46.155
Perfect.

41:47.809 --> 41:51.073
Actually, you know what?
Go, go back a little bit.

41:51.117 --> 41:55.208
That's it. That's it! Nice.

41:55.251 --> 41:57.471
This guy is awesome. I mean,
he's basically a level eight.

41:57.515 --> 41:59.473
-[Claire] I know.
-[Paul chuckles]

42:02.911 --> 42:04.783
Okay.

42:04.826 --> 42:08.003
Now look up to the light.

42:10.310 --> 42:12.181
That's life.

42:12.225 --> 42:15.881
It's bright, it's inviting,
it's warm.

42:15.924 --> 42:18.361
That's light. That's life.

42:18.405 --> 42:21.103
And this is death.

42:24.890 --> 42:26.587
What do you see?

42:28.067 --> 42:31.070
[Paul] I-I can still see
an outline.

42:31.113 --> 42:32.854
[Claire] But it's fading.

42:32.898 --> 42:34.247
[Cultist] Exactly.

42:34.290 --> 42:37.380
See, normally when someone dies,

42:37.424 --> 42:40.775
there's a little bit
of afterglow that lingers.

42:40.819 --> 42:43.430
But then unfortunately,
it just disperses

42:43.473 --> 42:45.171
into the ether.

42:45.214 --> 42:49.088
But thanks to the great Storsh,

42:49.131 --> 42:52.787
his chosen will bask
in the light of eternity.

42:52.831 --> 42:55.573
Just because the magical Storsh

42:55.616 --> 42:58.750
spilled his magical blood
in that bath tub,

42:58.793 --> 43:00.708
the bath tub is magical

43:00.752 --> 43:03.624
and will magically hold on
to the afterglow

43:03.668 --> 43:06.279
for all eternity.

43:06.322 --> 43:08.542
All of that in a bath tub?

43:12.677 --> 43:14.635
[grunts]

43:14.679 --> 43:16.681
[sighs]

43:19.988 --> 43:22.556
Would you like to bear witness
to my exodus?

43:31.739 --> 43:35.090
Cyanide. It's quick. Painless.

43:50.715 --> 43:52.717
Well... [gulps]

43:52.760 --> 43:55.154
I'm sorry, I didn't think
I would get emotional.

43:56.808 --> 44:00.289
You know, you two
are gonna be great followers.

44:00.333 --> 44:02.030
[Claire] Hm.

44:02.074 --> 44:03.641
I'm gonna tell Storsh about you

44:03.684 --> 44:06.121
when I get to the other side.

44:06.165 --> 44:08.080
-That's neat.
-[Claire chuckles]

44:10.648 --> 44:11.997
Yeah.

44:12.040 --> 44:13.302
Bye.

44:21.310 --> 44:23.051
It's just a sec.

44:33.409 --> 44:34.541
Any second.

44:40.765 --> 44:42.549
[coughing]

44:47.032 --> 44:49.077
-Oh! Oh! Ow! Whoa!
-Oh...

44:49.121 --> 44:51.558
Whoa, wait, hey,
this actually hurts quite a bit.

44:51.601 --> 44:53.778
-Oh, Go... Oh, no!
-Ah! Oh, God!

44:53.821 --> 44:55.997
Oh! Oh, actually,
this hurts quite a lot actually!

44:56.041 --> 44:58.696
-Do you want some water?
-Oh, for the love of Christ!

44:58.739 --> 45:01.046
[screaming]
They're inside of my body,

45:01.089 --> 45:02.656
burning like a thousand suns!

45:02.700 --> 45:04.702
-No! Oh, no!
-I'll go get a first-aid kit!

45:04.745 --> 45:06.747
-No! You idiot!
-[screaming]

45:06.791 --> 45:09.663
I wanna die! Kill me!

45:09.707 --> 45:10.838
-Kill me!
-Just go!

45:10.882 --> 45:11.926
Oh, my God!

45:11.970 --> 45:13.711
[screaming]

45:17.105 --> 45:18.759
Use this! Use this!

45:18.803 --> 45:20.239
-Me?
-Yes!

45:20.282 --> 45:21.849
Oh! Oh!

45:21.893 --> 45:23.459
[groaning]

45:25.157 --> 45:27.289
-I am sorry!
-[screaming]

45:27.333 --> 45:28.508
[grunting]

45:28.551 --> 45:31.032
What kind of cheap knife
is that?

45:31.076 --> 45:32.773
-We're on a budget, okay?
-No!

45:32.817 --> 45:35.341
-Stab harder! Do it!
-[grunting]

45:35.384 --> 45:37.299
[screaming]

45:41.913 --> 45:44.002
-Come on!
-No!

45:44.045 --> 45:46.047
Oh! Claire, stop it!

45:46.091 --> 45:49.703
-Stop! Claire, no!
-[screaming]

45:49.747 --> 45:51.444
We need better killing!

45:51.487 --> 45:53.402
[groaning]

45:55.578 --> 45:58.364
Oh, God! You can't kill me
with that stapler!

45:58.407 --> 46:01.149
-Oh, God! Aah!
-Oh!

46:01.193 --> 46:03.848
[cultist] You have no idea
how much this hurts!

46:03.891 --> 46:05.414
Plug it in!

46:05.458 --> 46:07.025
[cultist screams]

46:07.068 --> 46:08.417
[choking]

46:08.461 --> 46:10.376
Why won't you die?

46:13.858 --> 46:15.816
I gotta get 'em out!

46:15.860 --> 46:18.036
[groaning]

46:18.079 --> 46:19.689
[grunting]

46:19.733 --> 46:20.690
Oh!

46:23.781 --> 46:25.086
[camera shutter clicks]

46:30.352 --> 46:32.964
Is there something
you wanna tell me, Claire?

46:33.007 --> 46:35.880
Uh, no, I-I don't think so.

46:35.923 --> 46:38.317
You're sure about that?

46:38.360 --> 46:40.275
Yeah, I'm pretty sure.

46:41.189 --> 46:42.147
[scoffs]

46:43.757 --> 46:45.890
I get why you would,
but it's not a good idea

46:45.933 --> 46:47.892
to lie to a detective, it's...

46:47.935 --> 46:49.763
I detect.

46:49.807 --> 46:53.419
I get to the bottom of things.
It's my job.

46:53.462 --> 46:55.682
And your job is,

46:55.725 --> 46:58.380
you work in the business.

46:58.424 --> 47:00.295
-The business?
-Yeah.

47:00.339 --> 47:02.558
The ad business? I found out.

47:02.602 --> 47:05.039
You work at Global Creative.

47:05.083 --> 47:08.738
Okay, come on. I-I...
Let me wet my beak.

47:08.782 --> 47:12.133
Do you understand how you could
help a person in my situation?

47:12.177 --> 47:14.266
Just...

47:14.309 --> 47:16.703
[Paul] Oh, hey! Is this
your screenplay? Cool!

47:16.746 --> 47:18.966
[Cartwright] I didn't exactly
pick a title yet, but...

47:19.010 --> 47:22.143
Well, what exactly
do you want me to do with this?

47:22.187 --> 47:23.884
Well, do what you do.
Talk to people.

47:23.928 --> 47:26.844
You must know actors, right?
D-do you know Wesley Snipes?

47:26.887 --> 47:28.976
He's who I always picture
when I'm writing about myself.

47:29.020 --> 47:31.196
Uh, he needs this.

47:31.239 --> 47:35.417
Yeah. Totally. I...
You know, I'll make some calls.

